http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Honour-for-Muneer/article14001427.ece

Panchayat and Social Justice Minister M.K. Muneer has been chosen for the award instituted by the Kerala Institute of Local Administration. Dr. Muneer has been chosen for the award for his ‘continued and sustained leadership for strengthening democratic decentralisation, empowering local self governments and for charting further course of action as rights based development.’ Carl Wright, Secretary General, Commonwealth Local Government Forum, would present the award to Dr. Muneer at a function to be held at Kerala Institute of Local Administration (KILA) on January 21.Corrections & Clarifications:This article has been edited for a factual error.